Robert Blake faced accusations of killing his wife, Bonny Lee Bakley, in a complex trial filled with twists.
Witnesses detailed Blake's desire to keep his daughter, Rosie, while distancing himself from Bakley.
Prosecutors argued that Blake orchestrated his wife's murder after failed attempts to hire hitmen.
Defense attorney Schwartzbach dismissed key witnesses as unreliable, painting Bakley as a manipulative figure.
The trial featured humor and dramatic moments, with the defense mocking the absurdity of the alleged murder plot.
Ultimately, the jury had to weigh Blake's guilt in a case that resembled a sensational crime novel.
